{"Content-Encoding":"UTF-8","Content-Length":"90597","Content-Type":"application/xhtml+xml; charset\u003dUTF-8","Content-Type-Hint":"text/html; charset\u003dUTF-8","X-Parsed-By":["org.apache.tika.parser.DefaultParser","org.apache.tika.parser.html.HtmlParser"],"dc:title":"Yale agrees to return Machu Picchu artifacts to Peru, ending dispute | La Plaza | Los Angeles Times","description":"Yale University has agreed to return thousands of pre-Hispanic artifacts to Peru, tentatively ending a dispute that pitted the Ivy League school against a growing demand in the Andean nation to reclaim its \"cultural patrimony.\" The Machu Picchu objects -- including pottery, textiles and human bones -- have been in Yale\u0027s hands for nearly a century, since Hiram Bingham III, a Yale historian, first \"rediscovered\" the ancient Inca city in 1911. Peruvian President Alan Garcia and his predecessor, Alejandro Toledo, had made it a priority to pressure the university to release the excavated pieces, saying they were merely moved out of the country on loan between 1912 and 1915. Yale had refused for years, saying many Machu Picchu pieces were returned in 1921 and that it had been established then that the rest would stay at the university\u0027s Peabody Museum in New Haven, Conn. In a statement over the weekend, Yale said it was pleased with developments in recent talks and was still working out details on how to transfer the first batch of objects to San Antonio Abad University in the city of Cuzco as early as next year, after an inventory is completed and a new research center...","keywords":"peru, yale, artifacts, machu picchu, inca, dispute, archeology, anthropology, discord, case, hiram bingham","msvalidate.01":"AAC9C18F70AC386BC4DCF4DDF9BF1786","resourceName":"208D51950229634FBBB9C7E7225DDF1C_Yale_agrees_to_return_Machu_Picchu_artifacts_to_Peru,_ending_dispute___La_Plaza___Los_Angeles_Times.htm","title":"Yale agrees to return Machu Picchu artifacts to Peru, ending dispute | La Plaza | Los Angeles Times","y_key":"6427f578aa9f5a5d"}